Solanum carolinense is a species of flowering plant in the nightshade family.
It is also known as Carolina horsenettle or bull nettle.
The plant has a spiny stem and leaves that are oblong or oval in shape.
The flowers of Solanum carolinense are star-shaped and can be white or pale blue in color.
The fruit of the plant is a berry that is yellow or orange in color when ripe.
Solanum carolinense is often considered a weed and can be found in fields, roadsides, and other disturbed areas.
In traditional medicine, the plant has been used to treat conditions such as diarrhea and skin ulcers.
